   <h1>RE: [T2] Gathering group to help engine drop  (Troy's bus)</h1>
   <b>Chris Mills <scm9985(-at-)tntech.edu></b><br/>
   <i>2002-04-30 22:05:45+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>Indian Head gasket goop. It is a thin dark colored "glue" that an old 
mechanic I knew swore by. You can still get it - different brands and names.

It acts like a sealant and a light glue and I have taken to applying it to 
everything including the seating surface of crank and shaft seals.

Can't hurt and I think (THINK) it keeps my motors a little bit drier. You 
can also apply it to studs and such...


>Chris,
>         I have the seals already (From Busted Bus, thanks Joe!).  Here
>is the list of parts that I already have.  I am going to do the both the
>seals for the engine and tranny while  at the same time.  Any
>suggestions to other items that I should have are welcome.  Thanks
>
>Flywheel Washer
>Clutch Disk
>Rear Main Seal-Tranny
>Flywheel O-Ring Seal
>Rear Main Seal
>
>Troy Wical
>troy(-at-)wicals.com
>www.wicals.com
>'78 Transporter
>
>
>-----Original Message-----
>From: Chris Mills [mailto:scm9985(-at-)tntech.edu]
>Sent: Tuesday, April 30, 2002 4:02 PM
>To: Troy; Type2(-at-)type2.com
>Subject: RE: [T2] Gathering group to help engine drop (Troy's bus)
>
>
>The engine and tranny have to be separated but the engine does not have
>to
>come apart if it is the rear main seal (which it sounds like).
>
>It will simply require engine removal, flywheel and clutch removal.
>
>New seal - grease it where the seal touches the crankshaft.
>
>Back together.
>
>You can get this seal from any FLAPS.
>
>At 03:22 PM 4/30/02 -0400, you wrote:
> >I was told by someone that it has to be split to replace either the
> >main or rear main seal.  Can't remember which one.  I personally do not
>
> >know what needs to be done.  (I have been reading the engine drop
> >procedure in Bentley and stuff in the archives and have not run by this
>
> >either.) If that person is wrong, that would be fine by me.  :)
> >
> >Troy Wical
> >troy(-at-)wicals.com
> >www.wicals.com
> >'78 Transporter
